Timothy Omotoso says he'll feel ambushed in his new trial if he's not provided with additional details about the more than 90 charges he's facing. Courtesy #DStv403 PORT ELIZABETH - Nigerian pastor Timothy Omotoso and his co-accused are back in the Port Elizabeth High Court on Monday. They're facing human trafficking and rape charges, among others. READ: Omotoso deemed a 'prohibited person' They allegedly trafficked dozens of girls and women from various branches of his church to a house in KwaZulu-Natal. Last week, the court dismissed the defence's application questioning whether it had the jurisdiction to deal with other charges against the accused. READ: 'I don't want to feel ambushed': Omotoso It ruled that the court had the authority to preside over the whole matter.